## DATA STRUCTURES 
 ## key points
 - Data structure is the way of organizing the data to perform effecient update,search,delete,Insert operations.
 - It is used to manage the storage properly without wasting the memory.
 - There are two types of DS:

                    Data Structures
                          |
         ---------------------------------
         |                               |
    Primitive                     Non-Primitive
                                      |
                    --------------------------------
                    |                              |
                Linear                       Non-Linear
                    |                              |
      -------------------------         -------------------
      |     |      |      |            |        |        |
    Array Linked  Stack Queue        Tree    Graph    Heap
           List

- Primitive DS: 
    ->byte
    ->short
    ->int 
    ->long
    ->double
    ->float
    ->char
    ->boolean

- Non-Primitive DS:
    These are built on the basis of primitive data types

    -Linear DS:
        -> The data is stored in sequential manner.

    -Non-Linear DS:
        -> The data is not stored in sequential manner.

## Learnings

- Data structures are used to store data properly so that accessing,deleting etc will be faster.
- Linear DS is sequential in manner.
- Non linear is not sequential in manner.
